I'm now focusing on integrating the logout button stylistically.  I'm aiming for visual consistency with the existing button style in the profile section. I'll use similar padding, font size, and color (a subtle red) to ensure a cohesive look. The button will have a clear label "Cerrar Sesión." This design should blend well with the existing elements, making it intuitive for the user. I'll keep it concise and visually consistent.


**Integrating Logout Functionality**

I'm now transferring the `handleLogout` from the modal, and using `signOut` and `auth` from Firebase. I'll confirm logout using `window.confirm`. I'm updating `HomeScreen.tsx` to handle the removal of the button from the modal. Next, I am going to add the button below the profile icon. The button will use similar styling to maintain the consistency of the design.



